Class TokenRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.cassandra.thrift.TokenRange
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<TokenRange>, org.apache.thrift.TBase<TokenRange,TokenRange._Fields>

    public class TokenRange
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.thrift.TBase<TokenRange,TokenRange._Fields>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<TokenRange>
    A TokenRange describes part of the Cassandra ring, it is a mapping from a range to endpoints responsible for that range.
